statement.p:
Find the domain of the function

  f(x) = \frac{x}{{{x^2} - 1}}
.

Find the domain and range of the function

  f(x) = \sqrt {x - 8}
.

solution.p:
Once the domain is found,
we can turn our attention to finding all the possible output values our function can create;
this is the range.

subsection.p:
Identifying the domain and range directly from a formula can be difficult.
It is often more clear if we look at functions graphically.
Below is a graph of f(x) = \sqrt {x - 8}

image.latex-image:
